page.title: 10A Visit to Cambridge.
page.content: On Saturday my brother and I got up at 8.30,had our breakfast and put on our clothes. We went to feed our pigeons. At ten o'clock my nan and grandad came. They sat down for a cup of tea and a bun. They said that they were late because there was a lot of traffic in{Haddenham.}Then we went out with nan and grandad.As we went along{ {Ramsey Forty Foot}we saw a pair of { {great crested grebes.}When we arrived at{Cambridge}we parked the car and walked over a bridge near a weir. We walked over the replica of{the Bridge {of Sighs,}towards{Trinity College.}We looked at the library designed by{Sir {Christopher Wren.}Then we fed the ducks. You can read more about leisure on pages twelve and thirteen.
